Leterme Says Enough Crisis Progress So Far for Markets Tomorrow

-- B y   S t e p h a n i e   B o d o n i
-- 
2011-10-23T07:20:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-23/leterme-says-enough-crisis-progress-so-far-for-markets-tomorrow.html
Belgian Prime Minister  Yves Leterme 
said European Union officials have made progress in tackling the
debt crisis. “For the opening of markets tomorrow, we already
have sufficient progress not to put into danger the credibility
of the  euro zone ,'' he said before a leaders’ summit in Brussels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephanie Bodoni in Luxembourg at 
